description:
Join Netguru Talent Marketplace , a proven partner for tech-minded freelancers and experts. Thanks to us, you will have access to various project-based opportunities and can collaborate with different companies and industries. As a result, you will not only gain more experience but also develop a variety of skills you didn’t even know you had. Work the way you like, on your terms, with no strings attached.

Currently, we are looking for a Conversion Analyst who would like to join one of our key long-term projects within the banking industry and develop a lasting relationship with our client - a leading player on the market.

Ready to apply? First check if you:
• Are open to work at least once per month from the office in Wrocław,
• Have at least 3 years of experience in web optimization environment,
• Have a good understanding of the user journey across the web and mobile,
• Are able to conduct A/B tests ,
• Have experience in cooperation with various stakeholders... (business/marketing/tech teams),
• Have experience in working in data-driven environments,
• Are expert in web analytics, Adobe Target, Adobe Audience Manager (Adobe suite/Google suite CRO tools),
• Have a strong command of written and spoken English (it's going to be your working language).
We'll be happy to see that you have:
• Related educational background (marketing),
• Expertise with additional tools like - Insights, Chatbox or other CRO tools.
Your main responsibilities:
• using qualitative data (surveys, usability tests etc.) and quantitative data (web analytics) to derive insights, develop hypotheses, build and execute A/B tests and experiments and to propose data driven website optimization initiatives;
• driving experimentation, from managing backlog, to prioritization, QA, pre- and post-test analysis etc.;
• creating prototypes;
• developing engaging and conversion optimized landing pages with strong focus on generating prospect engagement and leads on the client website;
• leading website optimization and website redesign projects with focus on maximizing the lead generation output;
• close collaboration with different teams: marketing, publishing, research and IT etc.
• be an ambassador for experimentation excellence and a subject matter expert in your field as a part of the Agile squad covering a range of various skills.
Joining the project means:
• becoming a part of the Centre of Excellence Team, working with an advanced and highly experienced specialists;
• contributing to a long-term fintech project for one of our major clients;
• being engaged in discussions with key company stakeholders;
• developing and improving your skills rapidly;
• ensuring high-quality results.

Looking for a full-time job? Check out our Career Page and find out more about our open recruitment processes.

If you need any disability-related adaptation at any step of the recruitment process – simply let the recruiter know We'd be happy to help.

About the role

As Commercial Business Analyst you will work closely with Sales and Marketing Team providing data and information relevant for bid/no bid decisions, improvement of profitability, effectiveness and efficiency of the business in CEE as well as with relevant Business Unit leaders in CEE by facilitating business reviews, providing project and decision support and insights into what is behind the numbers.

Commercial Business Analyst is a member of a wider Commercial Excellence Team CE, reporting to the Commercial Excellence Manager CEE and also supports the Country Business Leaders, primarily in BD Interventional in close cooperation with the counterpart in Central Europe.

Main responsibilities will include:

Develop and communicate a standardized business report package;

Regularly monitor sales and GP performance, communicate and comment to the Team;

Provide comments on sales force performance based on Salesforce.com data to the business;

Coordinate and provide... guidance on Pricing, develop and enhance tools for Sales Team;

Provide ad-hoc analysis, reports and project support according to business needs;

Manage the incentive process for the respective business unit (alignment with policy, follow-up, payout calculation)

Drive long term planning, annual budget, forecasting processes (incl. data entry to SAP BPC);

Support modelling of Business scenarios;

Provide business analysis support for Go to Market adjustments in CEE geography;

Regular business data communication to the CEE Management Team;

We expect that you have:

2-4 years experience in business analysis, including financial forecasting;

Experience with BI systems (PowerBI as an advantage), MS Office, especially Excel (pivot tables, advanced formulas), experience with SAP BPC is an advantage, experience with CRM systems (ideally Salesforce.com);

Strong business acumen and sense of ownership – ‘I am a part of my Business Unit’

Strong analytical and conceptual skills, enjoying to work with numbers, accurate, attentive to details;

Good communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to communicate with stakeholders at all management levels in matrix organization, likes interacting with people;

International outlook, cultural sensitivity and awareness, flexible attitude and ability to handle changing priorities;

Capable of working well autonomously and in a team environment also with teams in remote locations, self-motivated, eager to learn and ready to operate in changing environment;

Demonstrates drive to achieve results by supporting others and cooperating with other functions;

Academic record with a degree or equivalent in finance, business economics or relevant professional experience;

Fluency in spoken and written English and Polish is a must.

Click on Apply if this sounds like you

Why join us

Next Technology Professionals jest certyfikowaną agencją rekrutacyjną, która dostarcza swoim klientom najlepszych pracowników.

Dla naszego klienta poszukujemy kandydatów na stanowisko:
Data Architekt Miejsce pracy: 100% zdalnie Start: zgodnie z dostępnościąForma współpracy: B2B z Next, full-timeWynagrodzenie: 200 - 250 zł netto/h + VAT Firma / projekt: naszym klientem jest globalna firma świadcząca usługi księgowe, doradcze i audytorskie. Klient szuka specjalisty, który zaprojektuje migrację hurtowni danych do chmury (GCP lub Azure).

Stos technologiczny: GCP/Azure, Python, Databricks, Snowflake, MSSQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle.

Zakres obowiązków / Responsibilities
• Zaprojektowanie migracji hurtowni danych do chmury.

Oczekujemy/ We expect
• Doświadczenie w pracy na podobnym stanowisku;
• Znajomość GCP lub Azure.

Oferujemy / We offer
• Profesjonalne wsparcie NEXT w budowaniu ścieżki kariery (zawsze gotowi do rozmowy i pomocy - nigdy nie będziesz miał świadomości, że czegoś nie wiesz... nie wyjaśniłeś lub zostałeś pozostawiony w projekcie "sam sobie");
• Rozwój zawodowy, uczestnictwo w najciekawszych i najbardziej innowacyjnych projektach na rynku, realizowanych dla klientów będących liderami w swoich branżach w Polsce i na świecie;
• Transparentny i uczciwy model współpracy długofalowej (bezterminowy kontrakt B2B);
• Możliwość pracy zdalnej w 100%;
• Stabilne zaangażowanie długofalowe w teamie ludzi, którzy wiedzą co i w jakim celu robią ;-);
• Ekosystem dzielenia się wiedzą i rozwoju zawodowego;
• Elastyczne godziny pracy (do ustalenia - EU Time Zones);
• Poza wynagrodzeniem, nasz Klient oferuje również dostęp do swojego portfolio / bazy szkoleń.

Proces rekrutacyjny:
• Rozmowa telefoniczna z Next
• Rozmowa biznesowo techniczna z klientem.
• Rozmowa z klientem końcowym.
• Podjęcie decyzji
